news.title: Lucknow development body to construct housing complex in green corridor
news.para: LDA vice chairperson Indramani Tripathi instructed the members of Project Implementation Unit (PIU), constituted for the implementation of the project, to prepare a land bank after conducting a survey of the route.

news.title: Pay Rs 2.30 crore property tax in 15 days: civic body notice to Chandigarh railway station
news.para: The recovery notice mentioning the property tax for the financial year of 2022-2023 includes arrears the railway station has not deposited.

news.title: Mohali development body's EWS flat scheme in hibernation mode
news.para: In total, GMADA was planning to construct 22,000 flats for the EWS, for which the authority has already acquired 230 acres of land for the project. The Detailed Project Report (DPR) has already been prepared by GMADA.

news.title: Ghaziabad: 4,400 sale deeds worth Rs 55 crore registered during Navratri
news.para: During the same period in the last financial year, a total of 3,949 registries were executed that fetched the stamp and registry department Rs 39 crore.

news.title: YEIDA officials face suspension for 'collusion' with developer for OCs
news.para: YEIDA has recommended action against officials of four departments for giving incorrect reports favouring the developer after examining allegations of lack of amenities at a housing project.

news.title: Cidco extends application deadline for its housing scheme by a month
news.para: The last date for the online registration of applicants was October 3. However, in order to facilitate more and more citizens to avail the benefit of the affordable scheme, Cidco has made extension.

news.title: Delhi: 60 acres of prime real estate may be up for grabs in Sarojini Nagar
news.para: As part of the plan, it’s weighing the option of selling around 60 acres of land and constructed properties in Sarojini Nagar.

news.title: Star India renews lease for 450,000 sq ft headquarter in Mumbai
news.para: In addition to the 16 floors in Urmi Estate, the company has also leased the ground floor lobby, meeting room and studio area on the ground floor, as well as the mail room and terrace on the 8th floor of the adjacent Urmi Iconic Building, which is part of the same complex.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance appoints Vinay Gupta as CFO
news.para: "... the board of directors of the company approved the appointment of Vinay Gupta as Chief Financial Officer and Key Managerial Personnel of the company effective October 26, 2022," it said.

news.title: Rich mainland Chinese snap up luxury homes in Singapore despite tax hikes
news.para: Mainland Chinese buyers accounted for about one-fifth of the 425 luxury units - defined as costing more than S$5 million ($3.52 million)- sold from January to August this year.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of three companies on November 10
news.para: ​A total of ten properties of three companies will be auctioned at a reserve price totalling Rs 7.68 crore, according to a public notice issued by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi).

news.title: DPCC asked to serve show-cause notice to Parsvnath Developers over violation of norms
news.para: Delhi environment minister Gopal Rai, who was on a visit to the construction site as a part of the government's anti-dust campaign, said that the firm was found in violation of several guidelines, and was found to have kept only one anti-smog gun instead of four, that too outside the construction site.

news.title: Nashik's digital mapping to help in planning various development works
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) will be doing the mapping in five divisions of the civic body, covering almost 85% of the city.

news.title: Insurance platform Turtlemint leases 35,000 sq ft office near Mumbai airport
news.para: These companies have leased the space for a five-year tenure from Chalet Hotels, a K Raheja Corp company. The occupiers will be paying rentals worth around Rs 28 crore during the total term of the lease.

news.title: Nashik civic body commissioner seeks report on property tax levied on industries
news.para: The commissioner sought the report after the recent meeting with representatives of industries in which the latter had urged the civic body to reduce the property tax rates, which had been increased by the then municipal commissioner around four years ago.
